{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"mealy-pansy-keg","description":"Map the Pass-2 novelty sub-answers to a deterministic novelty score (mirrors validity),\nthen add the rising-floor decision: a finding is dropped iff NOVEL (novelty >= T_novel)\nAND low priority (< floor); CARRYOVER findings use the normal threshold; a novel\nhigh-impact + high-validity finding is preserved (and may block). Dropped novel findings\ngo to overflow/sidecar. The whole policy is deterministic — no LLM holistic severity.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Deterministic novelty score from the Pass-2 sub-answers in `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py`\n- [ ] Drop rule in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py`: novel AND priority<floor -> dropped(->sidecar); carryover -> normal; novel high-stakes -> preserved\n- [ ] Policy lives entirely in Pass-3 (no LLM severity in the decision path)\n- [ ] Unit tests over the decision math (carryover/novel x high/low)","id":"150b-2200-13e7-4629","parent_id":"7d43-49c5-bc4d-4926","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Pass-2: emit a structured novelty sub-answer set (prior-findings grounded)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782753970213740001,"uuid":"b6663354-682a-49da-8780-dc8ca4bac43a"}